      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Apply a thin, even layer of the bacitracin cream—about a pea-sized amount—to cover the entire area after cleaning. You don't need to douse it daily with Betadine; simply cleanse the wound gently with the diluted solution once a day to keep surface bacteria away. This targeted approach allows the cream to work without overly irritating the healing tissue. Keep a close eye on it, though, because rapid deterioration means you need to call your doctor right away.",
